:: StoryTitle
Ashfall: Roads of Ruin

:: StoryData
{"ifid":"F8A9C2D2-7F4C-415C-93F0-37A931E1CBB4","format":"SugarCube","format-version":"2.36.1"}

:: StoryStart
The sky is a perpetual, bruised purple, heavy with the memory of fire. Decades have passed since the Ashfall Cataclysm, when the world tore itself open and choked on its own burning heart. A fine, gray dust settles on everything—your worn coat, the rusted husk of a long-dead vehicle, the skeletal remains of a forest that will never be green again. You are a Wanderer, a survivor defined by the road itself. Your origins are a story told in the set of your jaw and the caution in your eyes.

Tucked inside your gear is a fragile prize: a scorched piece of synth-parchment, a map fragment. Whispers in the few settlements brave enough to trade speak of Haven-0, a mythical pre-Cataclysm facility that could cleanse the sky. This fragment, stolen from raiders during a blinding ash storm, is said to be the first of four keys to finding it. The weight of it is immense. It is either a map to salvation or a warrant for your death, depending on who learns you carry it.

Ahead, the wastes stretch out, a monochrome expanse of rolling ash dunes and jagged rock formations. The wind carries a low, constant moan, a sound that is both a warning and a companion. Your immediate goal is clear: survive the next few miles, find shelter before the next toxic squall hits, and decide where to begin the impossible search for the remaining fragments. The road forks here, not just in the dirt under your boots, but in the choices you must make.
[[Press on toward the distant glow of a settlement's lights->AshDunesSettlementGlow]]
[[Follow a set of fresh tracks leading into a rocky canyon->AshDunesCanyonTracks]]
[[Head for a skeletal communication tower on the horizon->AshDunesCommTower]]
:: AshDunesSettlementGlow
The glow resolves into flickering electric lanterns strung along a high wall of scrap metal and packed earth. This is the Outpost of Last Hope, a name that sounds more desperate the closer you get. The main gate is a massive door of welded vehicle parts, currently open just a crack. Two guards in patched enviro-suits watch your approach, their rifles held with a weary readiness.
[[Approach the guards and request entry->OutpostGate]]
[[Skirt the walls, looking for another way in or a sign of the Nomads->OutpostWalls]]

:: AshDunesCanyonTracks
The tracks are deep, made by the wide, treaded tires of a large vehicle—a land-train, most likely, used by the militaristic Steel Legion. They lead into the shadows of the canyon. The air grows still and cold. Around a bend, you find the source: a Legion scout vehicle, its engine silent. It's parked near the entrance to a small cave. There are no signs of the crew, but the vehicle's hatch is open.
[[Investigate the abandoned scout vehicle->CanyonScoutVehicle]]
[[Enter the cave to look for the missing crew->CanyonCaveEntrance]]

:: AshDunesCommTower
The tower is a relic, a rusting finger pointing accusingly at the dead sky. A rickety ladder ascends into the superstructure. At its base, the ruins of a control building have been partially reclaimed by the dunes. A faint, rhythmic beeping sound emanates from within the rubble, a stubborn electronic heartbeat.
[[Climb the tower to get a vantage point->CommTowerTop]]
[[Search the ruined control building for the source of the beeping->CommTowerRuin]]

:: OutpostGate
One guard steps forward, her visor raised to reveal a tired face. "State your business, Wanderer. We're not taking on extra mouths to feed unless you've got something to trade." She eyes your gear, her gaze lingering on the bulk of your pack where the map fragment is hidden.
[[Offer to trade scavenged parts->OutpostGate-Trade]]
[[Mention you're looking for information on old-world facilities->OutpostGate-Info]]
[[Ask about the Dustborn Nomads->OutpostGate-Nomads]]

:: OutpostGate-Trade
You lay out some usable circuitry and a clean water filter. The guard nods, satisfied. "Alright. You can come in. Keep to the main market, don't cause trouble." She steps aside, allowing you entry into the bustling, crowded interior of the outpost.
[[Enter the outpost->OutpostMarket]]

:: OutpostGate-Info
The guard's eyes narrow. "Old-world facilities are a good way to get killed. The Union boys in their bunkers might know, or the Legion hunts for that stuff. But asking those questions here marks you as either very brave or very stupid." She gestures for you to enter, but her watchfulness has intensified.
[[Enter the outpost cautiously->OutpostMarket]]

:: OutpostGate-Nomads
"A Nomad skiff passed by this morning, heading west toward the Salt Flats. They don't often stop here," the guard says. "If you're looking to catch them, you're behind schedule." She seems curious about your interest but ultimately waves you inside.
[[Enter the outpost->OutpostMarket]]

:: OutpostWalls
Moving silently along the perimeter, you find a section where the wall is lower, shielded by a pile of debris. A small, grimy face peeks out from a gap in the scrap. It's a child, who quickly puts a finger to their lips and gestures for you to follow. They duck into a hidden tunnel.
[[Follow the child into the tunnel->OutpostHiddenTunnel]]

:: CanyonScoutVehicle
The vehicle is unlocked and empty. The console is powered down, but a datapad lies on the pilot's seat. Its screen displays a partial log entry: "...investigating anomalous energy signature. Possible Union activity. Proceeding on foot. Captain Hale will want..." The rest is cut off.
[[Take the datapad->CanyonScoutVehicle-HasDatapad]]
[[Leave the datapad and continue into the cave->CanyonCaveEntrance]]

:: CanyonScoutVehicle-HasDatapad
You slip the Legion datapad into your pack. It could be useful, or it could be a death sentence if found on you. The cave mouth ahead seems darker, more foreboding.
[[Enter the cave->CanyonCaveEntrance-HasDatapad]]
:: CanyonCaveEntrance
The cave is damp and cool, a stark contrast to the dry waste outside. Faint, echoing voices can be heard from deeper within. As your eyes adjust, you see two Legion soldiers standing over a third person who is kneeling on the ground—a woman with sharp features and garments made of layered, ash-resistant cloth.
[[Step forward and intervene->CaveConfrontation]]
[[Stay hidden and observe->CaveObservation]]

:: CanyonCaveEntrance-HasDatapad
The cave is damp and cool. You hear voices. Two Legion soldiers are interrogating a sharp-featured woman in ash-resistant cloth. Having the datapad makes you acutely aware of your connection to this scene.
[[Step forward and intervene->CaveConfrontation-HasDatapad]]
[[Stay hidden and observe->CaveObservation-HasDatapad]]
:: CommTowerTop
The view from the top is vast and desolate. To the west, you see the glittering salt flats. To the east, the jagged line of the Rust-Ridge Mountains. A flicker of movement catches your eye: a convoy of armored vehicles—Steel Legion land-trains—moving fast along a dust-choked road, heading north. Then, a voice from below: "Enjoying the view, scavenger?"
[[Look down to see who spoke->CommTowerTop-MetLyra]]

:: CommTowerTop-MetLyra
A woman stands at the base of the ladder. She wears a hooded coat and carries a staff adorned with scavenged tech. "That Legion convoy isn't on a sightseeing tour," she says. "They're hunting. You might want to come down before they decide this tower is a strategic asset." Her eyes are keen, intelligent.
[[Climb down to talk to her->CommTowerBase-MetLyra]]

:: CommTowerRuin
Digging through the rubble, you find a sealed storage locker. The beeping is coming from inside. It's a Union-made distress beacon, still active. Forcing the locker open, you find not just the beacon, but also a small, hardened data-chip labeled "GeoCore Survey 7."
[[Take the data-chip->CommTowerRuin-HasDataChip]]
[[Leave the chip and only take the beacon->CommTowerRuin-HasBeacon]]

:: CommTowerRuin-HasDataChip
The data-chip feels heavy with potential. You pocket it and the beacon. As you turn to leave, a shadow falls over the doorway. A woman with a tech-adorned staff stands there. "That's a dangerous piece of history you've found," Lyra says.
[[Face the newcomer->CommTowerRuin-MetLyra]]

:: CommTowerRuin-HasBeacon
You take the beacon, leaving the data-chip behind. A shadow falls over the doorway. A woman with a tech-adorned staff stands there. "A beacon? Someone's been waiting a long time for a rescue that's never coming," she notes.
[[Face the newcomer->CommTowerRuin-MetLyra-Beacon]]

:: CommTowerRuin-MetLyra
"I'm Lyra. Some call me Ashwitch. I can read the storms in the data-streams," she says, gesturing to your pocket. "That chip you found... it's part of a larger puzzle. The same puzzle you're working on, if the rumors about a map-bearing Wanderer are true."
[[Ask how she knows about the map->TowerRuinTalk1]]
[[Show her the map fragment->TowerRuinTalk2]]
:: CommTowerRuin-MetLyra-Beacon
"I'm Lyra," the woman says. "An Ashwitch. I read the storms. That beacon is old Union tech. A relic." She seems less interested than if you had found the chip. "The waste is full of ghosts. But you seek something more solid, don't you?"
[[Ask what she means->TowerRuinTalk1-Beacon]]

:: OutpostMarket
The market is a cacophony of barter and survival. Vendors hawk filtered water, reclaimed ammunition, and questionable protein paste. You notice a group of Dustborn Nomads in their distinctive woven robes at a stall, arguing quietly with a stern-looking man who has the bearing of a Legion officer.
[[Approach the Nomads->MarketNomads]]
[[Eavesdrop on the argument between the Nomads and the Legionary->MarketArgument]]
[[Head to a quieter part of the market to examine your map->MarketAlley]]

:: OutpostHiddenTunnel
The tunnel is tight and dark, emerging into a hidden alcove within the outpost walls. The child is gone, but a young woman sits there, sharpening a blade. She looks up. "The guards don't like strangers sneaking in. But the Legion pays them to be watchful, and I don't like the Legion. I'm Moth. You look like you're going somewhere important."
[[Introduce yourself->HiddenTunnel-MetMoth]]

:: HiddenTunnel-MetMoth
"Moth? Like the insect?" you ask. She smiles. "They find their way in the dark. I know paths the Legion and even the Nomads miss. If you're heading into the deep wastes, you might need a guide." She gestures to the map fragment you've unconsciously touched. "And I know a thing or two about old paper."
[[Accept her offer of guidance->HiddenTunnel-WithMoth]]
[[Decline politely, preferring to travel alone->HiddenTunnel-Alone]]

:: HiddenTunnel-WithMoth
"A guide could be useful," you admit. Moth's smile widens. "Good. We should leave before that Legion officer finishes his business. There's a back way out." She leads you through a series of hidden passages, away from the market's noise.
[[Follow Moth out of the outpost->WastelandTrail-WithMoth]]

:: HiddenTunnel-Alone
"I travel better alone," you say. Moth nods, her smile fading. "I understand. The road is jealous. Good luck, Wanderer." She melts back into the shadows of the alcove. You are left to find your own way out of the outpost.
[[Return to the market->OutpostMarket]]

:: CaveConfrontation
"You alright?" you call out, stepping into the light. The soldiers spin around, raising their rifles. The kneeling woman seizes the moment, kicking one soldier's legs out from under him. In the confusion, she rolls toward you. "A little help would be appreciated!" she yells.
[[Help her fight the soldiers->CaveFight]]
[[Create a distraction to help her escape->CaveDistraction]]

:: CaveConfrontation-HasDatapad
You step forward. "Let her go." The soldiers turn. One recognizes the datapad in your hand. "Thief!" he snarls. The woman uses their distraction to disarm one soldier. "Don't just stand there!" she shouts. The situation has escalated instantly.
[[Engage the soldiers->CaveFight-HasDatapad]]
[[Throw the datapad aside and flee with the woman->CaveEscape-HasDatapad]]
:: CaveObservation
You remain hidden. The woman is defiant. "The Legion has no authority here, Captain Hale," she spits at the taller soldier. "The energy signature is neutralized. You've found nothing." Hale backhands her. "The Technic Union will learn to cooperate, Lyra. One way or another." They bind her hands and lead her deeper into the cave.
[[Follow them stealthily->CaveTunnel]]
[[Retreat and exit the cave->CanyonExit]]

:: CaveObservation-HasDatapad
You watch as Captain Hale strikes the woman, Lyra. They bind her and move deeper into the cave. You have their datapad. If you're caught, it will mean death. But leaving her feels wrong.
[[Follow them carefully->CaveTunnel-HasDatapad]]
[[Leave the cave quickly->CanyonExit-HasDatapad]]
:: CaveFight
You charge the standing soldier, tackling him before he can fire. The woman, Lyra, expertly subdues the other. In moments, both Legionaries are disarmed and unconscious. Lyra gets to her feet, brushing off her clothes. "Timely intervention. I'm Lyra. And you've just made a powerful enemy. We should go."
[[Leave the cave with Lyra->CanyonExit-WithLyra]]

:: CaveFight-HasDatapad
The fight is brief and brutal. With the element of surprise, you and Lyra quickly overpower the soldiers. Lyra picks up the datapad you dropped. "Hale's personal log? This is valuable. Come on, we need to move before more show up." She leads the way out.
[[Exit the cave with Lyra->CanyonExit-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]
:: CaveDistraction
You knock a loose rock from the wall, creating a loud clatter. The soldiers turn toward the noise. Lyra instantly breaks free, sliding into the shadows behind them. She signals for you to follow her down a side passage. The soldiers, confused, give chase but soon lose your trail in the dark tunnels.
[[Follow Lyra to safety->CaveEscape]]

:: CaveEscape-HasDatapad
You hurl the datapad against the far wall. It shatters. "What did you do?" one soldier cries out, distracted. Lyra escapes her grip and pulls you down a narrow tunnel. "That was... dramatic," she says as you run. "I'm Lyra. Now, run!"
[[Escape with Lyra->CaveEscapeRoute-WithLyra]]
:: CaveTunnel
You follow the echoes of the Legion squad. The tunnel opens into a larger cavern illuminated by portable lights. There's a sealed door set into the rock, marked with the symbol of the Technic Union. Captain Hale is trying to force it open. Lyra is tied to a stalagmite, watching him with cold hatred.
[[Attempt a rescue now->CavernRescue]]
[[Wait for a better opportunity->CavernWait]]

:: CaveTunnel-HasDatapad
You trail the Legion squad to a Union-marked door in a large cavern. Hale is trying to breach it. Lyra is captive. Your possession of the datapad makes you feel complicit.
[[Stage a diversion to free Lyra->CavernRescue-HasDatapad]]
[[Use the datapad's knowledge to bluff your way in->CavernBluff]]
:: CanyonExit
You emerge from the cave alone, the sun a dull coin in the ash-gray sky. The Legion scout vehicle still sits silently. The encounter leaves you with a name: Lyra. And a faction: the Steel Legion, led by Captain Hale, is actively hunting for old-world tech.
[[Continue your journey north toward the mountains->RustRidgeFoothills]]
[[Head west to the salt flats, following the Nomad lead->SaltFlatsEdge]]

:: CanyonExit-WithLyra
Outside the cave, Lyra studies you. "You saved me from a unpleasant conversation with Hale. I owe you. I'm a technomancer, exiled from the Union. I know how to read the data on that map fragment of yours. If you're heading to Haven-0, you'll need my skills to decipher the rest."
[[Travel with Lyra->WastelandTrail-WithLyra]]
[[Part ways, trusting your own instincts->WastelandTrail]]
:: CanyonExit-WithLyra-HasDatapad
In the open air, Lyra hands you back the datapad. "Hale's logs mention a 'GeoCore Vault' in the Rust-Ridge mountains. That could be where another fragment is. I can help you find it, but we need to move fast. The Legion will be hunting us both now."
[[Accept Lyra's help and head for the mountains->RustRidgeFoothills-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]
[[Go your separate ways, taking the datapad's info with you->RustRidgeFoothills-HasDatapad]]
:: CaveEscapeRoute-WithLyra
You and Lyra exit the cave system through a hidden fissure, far from the canyon entrance. "That was close," she says, catching her breath. "I'm Lyra. It seems we're both on the Legion's list now. I can help you understand your map. The old symbols are a kind of code."
[[Join forces with Lyra->WastelandTrail-WithLyra]]
[[Thank her and continue alone->WastelandTrail]]
:: CavernRescue
You create a noise at the cavern's entrance. As one soldier investigates, you rush the other, freeing Lyra. Hale turns, drawing his sidearm. "Run!" Lyra shouts, and you both dash back into the tunnels, pursued by shouts and gunfire.
[[Escape the cavern->CaveEscapeRoute-WithLyra]]

:: CavernRescue-HasDatapad
You lure a soldier away, then ambush him. Freeing Lyra, you face Hale. He aims his pistol. "You have my property," he growls, meaning the datapad. Lyra throws a smoke pellet, and you vanish into the tunnels amid the confusion.
[[Escape with Lyra->CaveEscapeRoute-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]

:: CavernBluff
You step into the light, holding up the datapad. "Captain Hale! I've decoded the access sequence from your logs." Hale lowers his weapon, suspicious. "Is that so?" Lyra looks at you, stunned. You approach the door, praying your bluff works.
[[Attempt to open the Union door->UnionDoorBluff]]

:: UnionDoorBluff
[[Retreat back into the tunnels with Lyra->CaveEscapeRoute-WithLyra]]
:: WastelandTrail
The open wastes are silent save for the wind. You are alone with your thoughts and your goal. The path ahead is uncertain, but the map fragment is a constant weight, a promise or a curse.
[[Travel toward the Rust-Ridge mountains->RustRidgeFoothills]]
[[Head for the shimmering Salt Flats->SaltFlatsEdge]]

:: WastelandTrail-WithLyra
[[Travel toward the Rust-Ridge mountains->RustRidgeFoothills-WithLyra]]
[[Head for the shimmering Salt Flats->SaltFlatsEdge-WithLyra]]
:: WastelandTrail-WithMoth
Moth moves with a light, surefooted grace, pointing out safe paths through unstable ground and hidden water sources. "The Nomads say the second fragment is in a place called the Sunken Library," she says. "But it's in Ashen Choir territory. They don't like visitors."
[[Ask Moth about the Dustborn->TrailTalkMoth1]]
[[Ask about the Sunken Library->TrailTalkMoth2]]

:: RustRidgeFoothills
The mountains rise like the bones of the earth, sharp and forbidding. The air is thinner here. Below, you can see the massive, tracked vehicles of the Steel Legion carving a road through the valley. Their destination seems to be a specific peak.
[[Ascend the mountain, trying to stay ahead of the Legion->MountainAscent]]
[[Find a way to observe the Legion's activity from a hidden vantage->MountainVantage]]

:: RustRidgeFoothills-WithLyra-HasDatapad
"The datapad confirms it," Lyra says, looking at the Legion convoy. "They're heading for the GeoCore Vault. We need to get there first. There's a hidden ascent on the northern face, but it's dangerous."
[[Take the dangerous northern route->MountainAscent-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]
[[Let the Legion go first and look for an opportunity to slip in behind them->MountainVantage-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]

:: RustRidgeFoothills-HasDatapad
Alone, you watch the Legion convoy. The datapad's information points to the GeoCore Vault. Getting there before them or around them will be a challenge.
[[Attempt a swift, direct climb->MountainAscent-HasDatapad]]
[[Take a slower, stealthier path->MountainVantage-HasDatapad]]
:: SaltFlatsEdge
The salt flats are a blinding white expanse under the gloomy sky, a surreal landscape of crystalline structures and utter emptiness. In the distance, you see the familiar silhouette of a Nomad sand-skiff, its sails filled with the sluggish wind. It seems to be stopped, perhaps broken down.
[[Approach the Nomad skiff->NomadSkiff]]
[[Circle around the skiff, looking for signs of the Ashen Choir->SaltFlatsCircle]]

:: MountainAscent
The climb is grueling. Loose shale slides under your boots. Near the summit, you find a carved entrance into the mountain, sealed by a massive metal door bearing the GeoCore logo. It's intact, but there are recent scuffs around the lock—signs of attempted entry.
[[Try to find another way in->MountainSummitSearch]]
[[Attempt to force the lock->MountainDoorForce]]

:: MountainAscent-WithLyra-HasDatapad
The northern route is treacherous, a narrow ledge over a sheer drop. But it brings you to a hidden ventilation shaft leading into the mountain. "This is it," Lyra says. "An old maintenance access. The Legion won't know about this."
[[Enter through the ventilation shaft->GeoCoreVentEntry-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]

:: MountainAscent-HasDatapad
You push hard and reach the GeoCore door first. The Legion's attempts to open it are evident. Using information from the datapad, you might have a better chance.
[[Use the datapad to try and bypass the lock->MountainDoorDatapad]]
[[Abandon the door and search for another entrance->MountainSummitSearch-HasDatapad]]
:: MountainVantage
You find a good hiding spot with a view of the Legion's camp below. They've set up a perimeter around the main entrance. Captain Hale is there, barking orders. You also see a smaller, secondary entrance—a personnel door—lightly guarded on the far side of the camp.
[[Wait for nightfall to attempt a stealthy approach to the personnel door->MountainNightApproach]]
[[Create a diversion to draw the guards away from the personnel door->MountainDiversion]]

:: MountainVantage-WithLyra-HasDatapad
From your vantage, you and Lyra plan. "The personnel door is our best bet," she whispers. "But we need the guards gone. I can cause a power fluctuation in their comms equipment—a small distraction. It might be enough."
[[Use Lyra's distraction to sneak to the door->MountainDistractionEntry-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]
[[Wait for a natural shift in the guard patrol->MountainPatientEntry-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]

:: MountainVantage-HasDatapad
You observe the Legion camp. The personnel door is the weak point. You'll have to get past the guards alone.
[[Attempt a silent approach at night->MountainNightApproach-HasDatapad]]
[[Use a rock slide as a diversion->MountainDiversion-HasDatapad]]
:: NomadSkiff
As you get closer, you see the skiff is indeed disabled, its main rudder broken. A young Nomad is trying to repair it, looking frustrated. It's Moth, the courier from the outpost. She looks up, surprised to see you. "Wanderer! My luck might be turning. Can you give me a hand with this?"
[[Help Moth repair the skiff->SkiffRepair-MetMoth]]
[[Ask her why she's out here alone->SkiffQuestion]]

:: SkiffRepair-MetMoth
You help Moth secure the broken rudder with a spare part from your pack. She beams at you. "Thanks! This skiff is my life. Climb on, I'll give you a ride to the Library. It's faster than walking, and we can avoid the worst of the Choir's lookouts."
[[Join Moth on the skiff->SaltFlatsSkiff-WithMoth]]
:: SkiffQuestion
"I'm a courier," Moth says, still working on the rudder. "I carry messages between the Nomad clans and... sometimes others. It's risky. The Choir especially doesn't like outsiders. I heard you were looking for old-world things. The Library has many. And guards."
[[Offer to help with the skiff in exchange for information->SkiffRepair-MetMoth]]
[[Leave her to her work and continue on foot->SaltFlatsEdge-Alone]]

:: SaltFlatsCircle
Circling wide, you see a group of figures in gray, ash-caked robes approaching the skiff from the opposite direction—Ashen Choir zealots. They move with a silent, purposeful gait. Moth hasn't seen them yet.
[[Rush to warn Moth->SkiffWarning]]
[[Use the opportunity to sneak past both groups toward the Library->SaltFlatsSneak]]

:: GeoCoreVentEntry-WithLyra-HasDatapad
The shaft leads into a dark, dusty maintenance tunnel within the GeoCore Vault. The air is stale. Lyra uses a small light on her staff to illuminate the way. The tunnel opens onto a gantry overlooking a vast, underground cavern. Below, ancient machinery hums. In the center of the cavern, on a pedestal, glows a crystal data-shard—a map fragment. The main vault door remains closed.
[[Descend to the cavern floor->GeoCoreCavern-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]
[[Search the gantry for a control room->GeoCoreControlRoom-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]
:: MountainDoorDatapad
[[Enter the GeoCore Vault->GeoCoreVaultEntrance-HasDatapad-Datapad]]
:: MountainNightApproach
Under cover of darkness, you slip past the drowsy guards and reach the personnel door. It's locked, but a manual override panel is exposed. It requires a keycode.
[[Try to short-circuit the override panel->PersonnelDoorForce]]
[[Retreat and look for another way->MountainSummitSearch]]

:: MountainDistractionEntry-WithLyra-HasDatapad
Lyra focuses, and a Legion comms unit suddenly screeches with feedback. In the confusion, you both dash to the personnel door. Lyra quickly patches her datapad into the lock and it slides open. You slip inside just as the guards regain their composure.
[[Enter the vault->GeoCoreVaultEntrance-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]

:: GeoCoreCavern-WithLyra-HasDatapad
You approach the glowing crystal shard on its pedestal. A holographic figure flickers to life—Dr. Oren Vale. The fragment pulses with potential. The main vault door remains closed for now.
[[Take the second map fragment->GeoCoreFragmentTaken-WithLyra-HasDatapad-MetOren]]
[[Listen to the full message->ValeRecording-WithLyra-HasDatapad]]
:: GeoCoreConfrontation-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren
Hale levels his pistol at you. "The fragments, Wanderer. And the technomancer. You've cost me enough time." His soldiers fan out, surrounding you and Lyra. The situation is desperate.
[[Stand your ground and refuse->ConfrontationRefuse]]
[[Try to negotiate with Hale->ConfrontationNegotiate]]
[[Throw the fragments to the ground and make a break for it->ConfrontationFlight]]
:: GeoCoreEscape-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren
You and Lyra sprint back up the gantry to the maintenance tunnel. Legion fire ricochets around you. You scramble into the shaft just as the door closes behind you, sealing the Legion inside for a precious few moments. You have the fragment, but Hale has seen you, and he will not stop.
[[Escape the mountain->RidgeDescent-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren]]

:: SaltFlatsSkiff-WithMoth
The skiff glides silently over the salt, driven by the weak breeze. Moth points ahead. "The Sunken Library. It's not really sunken, it's just built low to the ground." A large, dome-like structure of stone and metal appears on the horizon. Ashen Choir sentries patrol its perimeter.
[[Approach the Library openly under a flag of parley->LibraryParley-WithMoth]]
[[Look for a hidden way in, avoiding the sentries->LibraryInfiltrate-WithMoth]]

:: LibraryParley-WithMoth
You and Moth approach with hands raised. A Choir Sentinel steps forward, his face hidden by a mask. "The texts are not for outsiders. Your presence defiles the sacred ash." Moth speaks up. "I have a message from the Eastern Clan! We seek only knowledge."
[[Try to persuade the Sentinel->LibraryPersuade]]
[[Moth's message causes a distraction, allowing you to slip inside->LibraryDistractionEntry]]

:: LibraryInfiltrate-WithMoth
Moth leads you to a collapsed section of the outer wall, hidden by a salt formation. You crawl through a narrow gap into a dark, dusty corridor within the Library. The air smells of old paper and incense.
[[Search for the fragment in the archives->LibraryArchives-WithMoth]]
[[Head toward the central chamber->LibraryCentral-WithMoth]]

:: LibraryArchives-WithMoth
The archives are vast, shelves stretching into darkness. Finding the fragment here could take days. Suddenly, a shadow detaches from the shelves. It's an old man, hunched and muttering to himself. He holds a glowing data-cube. "Vale said to protect it," he whispers. "Until the worthy one came."
[[Take the data-cube from the old man->LibraryFragmentTaken-WithMoth-MetOren]]
[[Talk to the old man->LibraryTalkOren]]

:: LibraryFragmentTaken-WithMoth-MetOren
You take the data-cube. The old man whimpers. This is the third fragment. You now travel with Moth and have met Dr. Vale.
[[Ask Vale to explain the nature of the Vault of Lament->ValeExplanation-WithMoth-HasMapFragment3-MetOren]]
:: RidgeDescent-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren
[[Set a course for the Forbidden Zone->ForbiddenZoneEdge-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren]]
:: ForbiddenZoneEdge-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren
You and Lyra stand at the edge of the nightmare landscape. The Forbidden Zone churns with violent energy storms. Lyra checks her scanner. "The storm activity is off the charts. Going in there is suicide without the right protection or a clear plan." The two map fragments in your pack hum insistently.
[[Press on despite the danger->ZoneStormEntry-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren]]
[[Search for a safe path or shelter->ZoneShelterSearch-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren]]
:: ZoneStormEntry-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren
You enter the storm. The world dissolves into howling wind and lashing energy. Lyra's tech fizzles. Visibility is zero. You are both thrown to the ground.
[[Be consumed by the maelstrom->Ending-DeathByStorm]]
:: Ending-DeathByStorm
The storm consumes you. Your body is scoured away by the ash, your map fragments lost to the wastes. Haven-0 remains a legend.
:: ZoneShelterSearch-WithLyra-HasMapFragment2-MetOren
