:: Haven0Entrance-WithMoth-WithLyra-WithOren-HasAllFragments
The massive, sculpted door of Haven-0 slams shut with a final, resonant boom, sealing out the cacophony of the faction war. You, Moth, Lyra, and Dr. Vale stand panting in the sudden, immense silence of the reception hall. The air is startlingly pure and cool, a shocking contrast to the ash-choked valley. Moth brushes gray dust from her robes, her eyes wide as she gazes at the soaring, pristine architecture. Lyra immediately scans the atrium with her tech-staff, its blue light gliding over smooth, unblemished walls. Dr. Vale stumbles forward, running a trembling hand over a console. "The life-support systems... still perfect," he whispers in awe. Ahead, a broad, descending corridor, illuminated by soft strips of light, leads into the heart of the arcology. The completed map in your hand has fallen silent, its guiding task complete. Only the final decision remains.
[[Proceed down the main corridor toward the control center->Haven0Core-WithMoth-WithLyra-WithOren-HasAllFragments]]

:: Haven0Core-WithMoth-WithLyra-WithOren-HasAllFragments
